# This scene contains information for the right sidebar.

= 🚧 Under development. 🛠️ 

**Expect bugs** 🐞 

🍀 Tell us where to find them. 

[? if progress > 6 : <h1>Knowledge: </h1> ?]

[? if progress > 6 : <details><summary>Complexity</summary><p>Complexity refers to self-organising systems that in contrast to machines we do not produce, but manage.</p></details> ?]

[? if progress > 7 : <details><summary>Whole Under Management</summary><p>The Whole Under Management is the “unit” you are managing and making decisions for. It is defined by three things: <br> • Decision makers <br> • Resource base <br> • Money </p></details> ?]

[? if progress > 8 : <details><summary>Decision makers</summary><p>Anyone who makes day-to-day decisions, carries them out, or has veto power over them. Being inclusive prevents hidden constraints later.</p></details> ?]


[? if progress > 9 : <details><summary>Resource base</summary><p>Everything you rely on to support your quality of life and plans. It includes physical resources (land, buildings, equipment) and human resources (people, partners, customers, neighbours, communities).</p></details> ?]

[? if progress > 21 : <details><summary>Holistic context</summary><p>Your Holistic Context is your shared “north star” for decision-making. It describes:<br> • The quality of life you want<br> • The future resource base needed to sustain it</p></details> ?]

[? if progress > 12 and part-of = "org" : <details><summary>Holistic context for organisations</summary><p>For organisations, the Holistic Context also includes a statement of purpose for the organisation.</p></details> ?]

[? if progress > 22 : <details><summary>Filter questions</summary><p>They are the seven context checks that help you test any action against your holistic context, so you avoid solutions that look good today but create problems tomorrow.</p><p>The seven checks are: <br> • Cause and Effect<br> • Weak Link (social, biological, financial)<br> • Marginal Reaction<br> • Gross Profit Analysis<br> • Energy/Money Source and Use<br> • Sustainability<br> • Gut Feel</p></details> ?]

[? if progress > 23 : <details><summary>When an action fails a check</summary><p>It does not automatically mean “never do it”. It means you have learned where the risk is. You can modify the action, choose a different action, or proceed knowing what you must monitor and control.</p></details> ?]

[? if progress > 33 : <details><summary>Why gut feel is last</summary><p>Because it uses the picture you built from the other checks. It asks how you feel about the action in terms of your values, relationships, and consequences for others.</p></details> ?]
